 In JavaScript, you can write a for loop using this syntax:

```javascript
for (initialization; condition; update) {
  // code to execute
}
```

Example: Loop from 1 to 5
```javascript
for (let i = 1; i <= 5; i++) {
  console.log(i);
}
```

